T*
() Tj
T*
(5.3src/federated_learning/server.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The server already contained a sequential and a parallel path, but the) Tj
T*
(experiment-specific configuration was not enabling the parallel branch. The final) Tj
T*
(configuration now activatesuse_parallel_training, and the server code was refined so) Tj
T*
(that the number of GPUs used can be capped explicitly viamax_parallel_gpus.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This change is important on a shared server because it allows controlled use of) Tj
T*
(hardware: the experiment can use two GPUs when appropriate, while still respecting a) Tj
T*
(project-level limit and avoiding accidental uncontrolled fan-out.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.4src/federated_learning/client.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The client-side training code was augmented with conservative DataLoader controls.) Tj
T*
(Specifically, the training arguments now) Tj
T*
(acceptdataloader_num_workers,dataloader_pin_memory, anddataloader_persistent_workerswhen) Tj
T*
(the installedtransformersversion supports them. For the final server-friendly) Tj
T*
(configuration, this was set to four workers per process.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The intent was not to saturate all 32 CPU threads on the machine, but to reduce) Tj
T*
(starvation of the GPUs and data-delivery stalls while keeping the experiment respectful) Tj
T*
(of a shared academic environment.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.5src/evaluation/evaluator.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The evaluator received the most important speed optimization. In the original evaluation) Tj
T*
(logic, the code tokenized and scored one text sample at a time in a serial loop. For a) Tj
T*
(test set with 250,000 flows, this would still be very slow and underutilize the GPU. The) Tj
T*
(new evaluator uses batched tokenization and batched inference, with optional autocast in) Tj
T*
(half precision. This change substantially reduces the runtime of the evaluation phase) Tj
T*
(and makes GPU usage much more meaningful.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The evaluator now also clears model objects and CUDA cache between rounds more) Tj
T*
(explicitly, which helps keep memory usage stable while iterating over all checkpoints.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
