T*
(The temporal table shows zero time-to-detection and full coverage for all rounds because) Tj
T*
(the selected thresholds cause nearly immediate detection once anomalous flows appear.) Tj
T*
(However, this apparently perfect temporal responsiveness is offset by an unacceptably) Tj
T*
(high benign false-positive rate, so it should not be interpreted as operational) Tj
T*
(readiness.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(13. Interpretation of the Final Results) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The final experiment demonstrates that the pipeline is technically functional and that) Tj
T*
(the model does learn a separation signal. F1 values around 0.69 on a balanced test set) Tj
T*
(confirm that the system is not random. The best checkpoint emerged early, around round) Tj
T*
(2, which means this setup converges quickly under the current training budget.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(However, the model?s operational profile is not yet satisfactory. The most striking) Tj
T*
(issue is the extremely high benign false-positive rate. For example, the best overall) Tj
T*
(K=1 result at round 2 achieved F1?0.6949 and recall?0.9907, but also a benign) Tj
T*
(FPR?0.8604. In plain terms, the system catches almost all anomalous traffic, but it) Tj
T*
(misclassifies a very large fraction of normal traffic as anomalous.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This means the current setup is useful as a proof-of-pipeline and as an experimental) Tj
T*
(baseline, but not yet as a production-quality anomaly detector. The most likely next) Tj
T*
(improvements would be threshold calibration on a benign-only calibration set,) Tj
T*
(alternative feature engineering forContent, larger or more representative training) Tj
T*
(subsets, and more operational threshold selection such as target-FPR tuning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(14. Files Added or Modified During This Work) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- configs/config_wifi.yaml: created and iteratively refined to control dataset loading,) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
